data.description: ***SOLAR PANELS & WATER SOFTENER WILL BE PAID OFF BY SELLER AT CLOSING***    This spacious two-story home located in the popular community of Saddlecreek has some of the best features to seek in a home! The high-ceiling in the family room illuminates a grand sense of spaciousness, the primary bedroom is located on the main floor, an office room with French doors is located next to the front entrance in the foyer, Cobblestone tile and carpet flooring, and covered back patio with a spacious backyard. The lot is measured at 0.196 acres and there is plenty of space in the backyard. The community of Saddlecreek provides amenities such as a resort-style pool, clubhouse, playscapes, walking trails, and is conveniently situated near Interstate-35 and Highway Toll 130. There is peace of mind knowing that access and distance to schools are very convenient because they are within close proximity of home. James Mitchell Elementary and Wagner Middle School are a 5-minutes drive away, and East View High School is an 8-minutes drive away. Solar panels on the roof will help save on energy costs and the water softener is also conveyed with the property. Both the solar panels and water softener will be paid off by the Seller at closing, so buyers will outright have ownership of both. The refrigerator will be conveyed and other non-realty items within the home are also negotiable, so during your tour please make note of what may be conveyed. If you would like to setup an appointment to tour this wonderful opportunity and/or have additional questions and concerns, please feel free to contact me!
